Salva Vida

This is a rescue dispatch app for calamities like Typhoon Yolanda.  It reads twitter streams for sos calls and plots them on a map.  Similar in functionality to rescueph.com but filters for dupes.

Example:

If a person is in trouble, tweet '@SalvaVidaPH/SOS/Name/Address' and a marker will be set on the map.
If a person is rescued, tweet '@SalvaVidaPH/Safe/Name/Address' and the marker will be removed.

Prerequisites: Go to dev.twitter.com and make an app to get the app keys, app secrets, oauth token and oauth token secrets

Add salvavida.cfg to your src/python/salvavida with the following contents:

[twitter]
app_key=<CONSUMER KEY>
app_secret=<CONSUMER SECRET>
oauth_token=<ACCESS TOKEN>
oauth_token_secret=<ACCESS TOKEN SECRET>
feed_tags=<KEYWORDS TO FILTER>

Start the twitter streamer with:
python src/python/salvavida/rescuefeed.py

Start the flask app with:
python app.py

